hello everyone, I notice that not everyone has been quite as busy as I.  I did get to go to so cal about a week ago.  It was great.  I saw my sis.  I am helping her with her wedding which has been a blast.  Also, since I am one of her bridesmaids we looked at dreses that don't make me look horrible.  I also have been going to the gym regularly.  I find it relaxes me. Wierd I know but it really does work out for the best.  I have found that the spin class is my friend I wish that I could do it everyday but knowing me I'd then get sick of it.  You know the saying if you always want more you wont get sick of it.  Also I got my nails done today.  And they are alittle too short and I hate that, but it's better than being too long then I can't do anything.  Well everyone I thought that I would say hi. and that I haven't forgotten about all of you but that I was gone and that I have been busy.  Well best wishes

Just had a coversation with D, by the way you didn't give us the number to the shop.  I hope that everything is going ok there.  Just remember beeee yourself.  Other than that I have been loving my new car. The only bad part has been feeding it.  It's not quite what I'm used to. hey everyone, life is great like normal, 2morrow is my 23rd b-day.  On a thursday how fun.  And my mom is taking me to do something that really doesn't intrest me in the least.  Have any of you heard of eyelash tinting? Well I will let you all know how that works out.  I'm kinda scared so wish me luck.  Oh and work has been great it is called not having to go, because I have been on call.  So they haven't needed me.  We meaning woo and I went ot the mimi's at Arden and we were treated horribly.  The waitress thought that we didn't even have enough money to even be there.  So we were ignored. Like normal when you are young and they really don't know anything.  The fun part is that when she handed us the bill.  I then gave her my pay check and asked for the bill to be modified.  Then it was like a lightbulb went off in her head.  Oh my god, this girl works at a mimi's then she it was day and night.  We were great and she kissed our ass after that.  Being that I was friends with the manager.  So that was wonderful.  She was sooooooo embarassed.  It felt great here honey have a piece of humble pie. thought all you should know


best wishes

hey everyone, alittle redendent I know but that works.  Today was a fun day at mimi's like normal.  Jeff did ask for his phone back. And wierdly enough it still hasn't shown up.  But truely would you forgive him???? I wouldn't and haven't. And probly wont.  I know that sounds kinda harsh, but I do feel that way even if it is alittle bitchy.  I can't help that so there.....  I love to throw temper tantrums.  And that my friends was it.  WOW, I know it's extreme...  Anyways I do have to work thanksgiving and that will be so much fun!!!! Yuck!!!!  A whole bunch of people who either don't know how to cook or just plain don't want to.  They all go a resturant and think that they are the only ones.  Needless to say, we were full for reso's by the 4th of this month.  How sad.  People make friends and find family.  HELLO.  Don't you think that those lovely people who wait on you at the resturants have families???  What if they had made plans and how nice of you to be so selfish.  Here have some humblepie and turkey and don't forget to come again.  Sill I'm not counting the people who did take-out dinners.  So just wondering does anyone know where their oven is?????  And is it really that hard to turn it to 250 degrees????  Plus we all know how hard it is to bast the turkey once an hour..  j/k Alright just a little of ranting and raving.  I understand that poeple need to go to the grocery store to grab things.  I guess it proves that most of the world has procrastinators in it...  I know I also can be one of them.  Can't we all... But!, if the stores and resturants in the world decided that one year that they were going to stay closed how many people would go hungry??  Let us count the hundreds of thousands around the U.S.  One... Two... Hundred....  j/k. Actually I'm not...  Nadia I though that you should know who I'm not talking to it's Mike...  Jeff and I are not talking with him.  He does have drinking problem and needs help the problem is that he doesn't see it or just doesn't want to be helped.  We all have tried but to no avail, if you can't tell.  So now there is no talking between us. And Jeff doesn't plan on changing that for some time.  Sorry to be the person with bad news..


best wishes,
chyanne

today I paid rent and we are now broke yet again...  Anyways I thought that I'd tell everyone that the girl that I am talking about not only is not able to sue me but called me a bitch in front of the regional manager.  Ha take that.  But I thought everyone who reads this would like to know.  I guess I'm not really all that bad.  My fav manager said that from now on we were going to share a section at work.  Ha ha ha very funny.  And that we are going to be in the same room just to piss her off.  I know that wont happen so thats alright.  I love my job at times but we all here know how much it can strain you.  At least they all stuck up for me when I really needed it.  Maybe it's because they can trust me and maybe because I'm not a flake.  What else oh my car is getting new tires 2morrow.  I'm excited it is fun driving the van but I would really like to have my own car back.  And Draven did give me new news about the jobs opening in this area which is awsome.  There are no bad things happening on the home front.  I do need a new washer and dryer but those can be found, hopefully easly.  If the money is there.  I could save my money and they will be bought.  Jeff and I are going to Hawaii next year and we are both very excited.  We are not quite sure where to go though.  I've been so it doesn't matter to me. IT does on the other hand feel good that I have been somewhere and Jeff hasn't.  The tables are turned in my favor for once.  At least there is no ranting and raving here tonight.  Wish me luck on tips 2morrow.

best wishes
